# Harness warmup (Grace-Mar)

New Cursor threads have **no memory** of `recursion-gate`, `self-archive` (EVIDENCE), or `session-log`. Warmup fixes that.

## When to run

At the **start of a new chat** when work touches **instance state** (pipeline, RECURSION-GATE, Voice, OpenClaw handoff, `users/grace-mar/`, bootstrap continuation):

1. Run from repo root:
   ```bash
   python3 scripts/harness_warmup.py -u grace-mar
   ```
   Use `--compact` if the operator prefers one paragraph. **`--territory work-politics`** (aliases: `pol`, `wp`; legacy `wap`) = work-politics pending only; **`companion`** = Record pending only (see `recursion_gate_territory.py`).

2. **Include the command output** in your reply (paste verbatim or as a fenced markdown block) so the thread carries the same snapshot.

**Optional one-line snapshot (not a second mandatory ritual):** When the operator wants a single grounded line (e.g. “receipt” / “heartbeat line”), run `python3 scripts/harness_warmup.py -u grace-mar --receipt` (combine with `--territory` as needed). **Do not** require this as the first line of every reply — that duplicates **hey** (operator-cadence **A–H**; optional under menu **H**) and conflicts with harness skip cases and PLAN-default in operator-style.

**One-command re-entry paste:** `python3 scripts/operator_reentry_stack.py -u grace-mar` runs handoff check, then `operator_daily_warmup` (operator-cadence Step 1), then harness (add `--compact` for a shorter harness tail). Output overlaps by design; use for cold threads, not minimal noise.

**Full “hey” stack:** When the operator says **hey** (including **multiple times per day** for reorientation — see operator-cadence § *Multiple heys per day*), run that skill’s steps. **Step 1** = read-only scripts + branch snapshot + defer lines — **no** Polymarket / web poll / Massie X internet pass until **menu E → work-politics** (or explicit same-message request). **KY-4 + Polymarket + polls** follow `docs/skill-work/work-politics/polling-and-markets.md` **only** on that path (or **C** for §1d Putin web when daily brief runs). Then **Step 2**: fixed **A–H** (list **A,B,C,D,E,G,H,F**) — **A** template + boundary audit (combined when chosen), **B** repository hygiene, **C** **Daily brief** — generator + §1d Putin **only when C is chosen**, **D** **RECURSION-GATE** (gate-review-pass; **no merge** without companion approval), **E** **work-dev *or* work-strategy *or* work-politics** — **E / work-politics** runs the intel stack when not survey-only; **G** work-jiang / Predictive History; **H** skills / meta pipeline (candidates, extract-skill, portable sync; optional receipt line); **F** end hey session. **“Hey survey”** → **E** defaults to **Companion survey** (see `.cursor/skills/operator-cadence/SKILL.md`) without forced Polymarket/Massie unless asked. After **A,B,C,D,E,G, or H**, **re-offer the full A–H menu** each turn until **F**. See `.cursor/skills/operator-cadence/SKILL.md` § *Hey — multiple choice (A–H required)*.

**Hey — closeout intent (session end):** When the operator says **`hey`** and means **signing off / closeout** (same skill, not a second trigger), follow `.cursor/skills/operator-cadence/SKILL.md` § **Hey — closeout** — **Step 1:** **`python3 scripts/operator_handoff_check.py -u grace-mar`** + summary paragraph; **Step 2:** fixed **A–H** menu (order **A,B,C,D,E,G,H,F**) — **A–D** match work-start **hey** (template + boundary, repository hygiene, Daily brief, **RECURSION-GATE**); **E** = **system pick** (integrity, survey, commit grouping, etc. — prefer **G** for Jiang/PH deep-dive, **H** for skills pipeline); **G** / **H** same roles as work-start **hey**; **F** = formally end closeout. After **A,B,C,D,E,G, or H**, **re-offer the full A–H menu** each turn until **F**. Do **not** substitute the full work-start **hey** stack unless they ask for it.

## When you may skip

- Operator says they’re only editing unrelated code/docs with no gate/evidence context.
- Warmup was already pasted in this thread.
- Trivial one-line fix with no Record/pipeline involvement.

## Relation to bootstrap

`bootstrap/grace-mar-bootstrap.md` = **procedure** (what to read, work-dev, commands). Warmup = **current state** (pending candidates, last ACT, session tail). They stack: bootstrap orients; warmup grounds.

**Stewardship:** Treat warmup output as a **weather report**, not policy — policy lives in `AGENTS.md`, RECURSION-GATE, and companion-approved merges.

## Do not

- Merge or stage from warmup output — it’s read-only context.
- Treat warmup text as Record truth; canonical files remain `users/grace-mar/*.md`.
